Hello?
<i>Yes, I'm here.</i>

25:13.885 --> 25:17.051
I still don't have
a damn negotiator,
and I'm wondering why.

25:17.086 --> 25:18.151
Where's my negotiator?

25:19.253 --> 25:20.791
Hello?

25:20.826 --> 25:22.221
<i>All right,</i>
<i>hang on just a second.</i>

25:23.730 --> 25:24.762
Hello?

25:31.738 --> 25:35.234
Sir, we can really help you.
Please, um-- Please don't!

25:36.204 --> 25:37.907
No, don't...

25:39.240 --> 25:41.372
I had a button made, okay.

25:41.407 --> 25:42.747
You see this?

25:44.047 --> 25:47.015
We got kids.
Please don't, sir.

25:47.050 --> 25:50.623
I need my negotiator. Somebody--
Somebody to come down and talk!

25:50.658 --> 25:52.383
To talk! That's all!

25:52.418 --> 25:55.320
Where's my negotiator?
Please, ma'am, just...

25:55.355 --> 25:58.862
<i>Sir. Just hold onto the phone</i>
<i>right here...</i>

25:58.897 --> 26:00.798
I've been holding on.
I've been holding on though.

26:00.833 --> 26:03.130
I've been holding on though.
I held on.

26:07.103 --> 26:09.972
<i>If we get disconnected,</i>
<i>I'll call you right back, okay?</i>

26:12.042 --> 26:12.874
<i>Okay?</i>

26:14.242 --> 26:16.308
You gonna have
my negotiator ready for me?

26:17.047 --> 26:19.080
Ma'am?

26:19.115 --> 26:21.115
<i>Yes, sir, you just</i>
<i>hold onto the line.</i>
Okay.

26:21.150 --> 26:23.150
<i>I'll get him on.</i>
Okay.

26:37.199 --> 26:39.298
I'm sorry, y'all,
I had to do that.

26:48.914 --> 26:50.881
Any of y'all ladies
need the restroom?

26:57.725 --> 27:00.660
-I could do to use the restroom.
-All right, go on then.

27:19.076 --> 27:20.108
You okay?

27:48.941 --> 27:51.370
Hello? Okay.
<i>I have Major Riddick</i>
<i>on the phone.</i>

27:51.405 --> 27:52.976
Okay.

27:53.011 --> 27:54.813
Check on Estel
in the bathroom, okay.

27:54.848 --> 27:56.276
Make sure she good, aight?

28:02.955 --> 28:04.790
<i>You there, sir?</i>
Uh, yes, I am.

28:06.354 --> 28:08.255
<i>Hello, Mr. Easley.</i>
<i>My name is Major Riddick.</i>

28:08.290 --> 28:10.191
<i>Now you tell us</i>
<i>what's going on in there, okay?</i>

28:10.226 --> 28:12.061
-The Department
of Veterans Affairs...
-Estel?

28:12.899 --> 28:13.931
Estel.

28:16.133 --> 28:19.035
They left me destitute
and homeless and, uh--

28:19.070 --> 28:22.269
I'm-- I'm going to
be on the streets.
So I need your assistance, sir.

28:22.304 --> 28:25.041
<i>All right.</i>
<i>What can we do to help you out?</i>

28:25.076 --> 28:27.241
Well, pay me my money.

28:27.276 --> 28:30.211
That's the whole reason why we
having this conversation, sir.

28:30.246 --> 28:32.785
<i>All right, how much--</i>
<i>how much is that exactly?</i>

28:36.318 --> 28:39.220
Estel, I think we're gonna be
on the TV. Turn it on.

28:39.255 --> 28:41.893
We're gonna be on
one of the channels.
Sorry about that.

28:41.928 --> 28:45.457
<i>Well, would you be willing</i>
<i>to come outside and talk--</i>
<i>talk to us about that?</i>

28:46.493 --> 28:48.427
Sir, I'm not coming outside.

28:48.462 --> 28:50.803
<i>All right,</i>
<i>what are your intentions</i>
<i>right now?</i>

28:52.906 --> 28:54.037
Well, uh,

28:55.373 --> 28:58.272
my intentions are
to blow up this place
if my demands aren't met.

28:58.307 --> 29:02.078
I told y'all before.
I don't know why I have to
repeat myself, but okay.

29:02.113 --> 29:05.147
Uh, you know, I'm serious, sir.
I will blow this place up, sir.

29:05.182 --> 29:07.347
<i>-Okay. Okay.</i>
-Oh, sir, most importantly,

29:07.382 --> 29:08.920
I want to
talk to my daughter.

29:08.955 --> 29:11.087
I can't seem to get through.
<i>All right.</i>

29:11.122 --> 29:15.058
<i>Call you back in a little bit,</i>
<i>Mr. Weasley, okay?</i>
Yeah, that is absolutely fine.

29:19.999 --> 29:21.130
Okay.

29:34.046 --> 29:36.145
What you think?
Think the conversation
was good?

29:36.180 --> 29:38.147
Yes.
I think it was
a good conversation. You?

29:38.182 --> 29:39.412
Yes.
Yeah.

29:40.085 --> 29:41.315
Yeah.

29:58.334 --> 30:00.268
Mom?
Mmm.

30:00.303 --> 30:02.501
Mama?
Mm-hmm.

30:15.483 --> 30:17.054
Mama.
Mm-hmm.

30:17.089 --> 30:19.122
Mom.
Mm-hmm.

30:19.157 --> 30:21.223
Someone must
really wanna talk
to you.

30:21.258 --> 30:23.929
Okay, baby. My phone...

30:25.163 --> 30:26.195
Okay.

30:27.660 --> 30:28.901
Okay.

30:29.365 --> 30:30.463
Let me see.

30:32.302 --> 30:34.005
Okay, baby.

30:34.040 --> 30:37.074
Hello.
<i> Hello, Cass?</i>

30:37.109 --> 30:39.307
Yes.
<i>I've been calling you</i>
<i>all morning.</i>

30:39.342 --> 30:41.078
<i>Why you ain't</i>
<i>pick up your phone?</i>

30:41.113 --> 30:43.410
All right, all right, all right.
I'm up now, all right?

30:43.445 --> 30:46.512
I just-- Why you call me
so many times?
It's not even your number.

30:46.547 --> 30:49.416
That's why you should have
picked up your damn phone.
I've been callin' and callin'...

30:49.451 --> 30:52.452
I had a patient die
at four o'clock this morning.
I'm gonna go back to sleep.

30:52.487 --> 30:55.422
Oh, no. Don't do that, okay?
Hey, look, uh...

30:58.394 --> 31:00.427
I'm in the middle
of something and, um,

31:02.200 --> 31:06.400
depending on how everything
works out, I-- I might
go to jail for a long time.

31:06.435 --> 31:09.337
Okay. Listen, Brian, I--

31:10.208 --> 31:11.570
Are you off your medication?

31:13.607 --> 31:15.079
Don't do that, Cass.

31:15.114 --> 31:17.983
<i>I was just calling</i>
<i>to tell you that</i>

31:18.018 --> 31:19.677
<i>if something</i>
<i>were to happen to me...</i>

31:21.285 --> 31:23.318
<i>I'm trying to do right, okay?</i>

31:23.353 --> 31:27.223
<i>I'm trying</i>
<i>to right something here,</i>
<i>and I'm in a little situation.</i>

31:27.258 --> 31:30.193
<i>And I just wanted you to know</i>
<i>I'm just trying to do</i>
<i>the right thing.</i>

31:30.228 --> 31:32.723
<i>I'm trying to make</i>
<i>the right decisions.</i>
Yeah...

31:32.758 --> 31:35.660
And I'm just trying to tell you
that everything I do...

31:37.169 --> 31:39.004
Everything I do
is for you and Kiah.

31:39.039 --> 31:40.335
Mm-hmm.
<i>Everything.</i>

31:40.370 --> 31:42.634
Yeah, well, uh, Brian,
I don't--

31:42.669 --> 31:46.737
I don't really know
where you're going with this,
so...

31:46.772 --> 31:50.048
I don't know what--
Okay, thank you.

31:55.385 --> 31:57.616
You know what, you right.
Put my daughter on the phone.

31:57.651 --> 32:00.520
<i>All right.</i>
<i>But don't you be spooking her</i>
<i>like you did.</i>

32:00.555 --> 32:02.522
I never spook our baby.

32:02.557 --> 32:05.360
<i>Yesterday you told her how</i>
<i>you got thrown on the street</i>
<i>in handcuffs.</i>

32:05.395 --> 32:07.659
She needs to know
how this world treats
people like us.

32:07.694 --> 32:10.761
<i>I'm just letting her know.</i>
<i>She's about to be</i>
<i>in the world herself.</i>

32:10.796 --> 32:13.302
Yeah, all right, Brian.

32:13.337 --> 32:15.700
I'm not going through this
with you again, all right?

32:16.472 --> 32:18.274
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

32:19.541 --> 32:21.112
Kiah!

32:21.147 --> 32:23.180
<i>Your father's on the phone,</i>
<i>Kiah.</i>

32:23.215 --> 32:24.984
Hey, she mad?

32:26.812 --> 32:28.515
<i>She got reason to be.</i>

32:35.656 --> 32:37.128
Cassandra...

32:38.731 --> 32:42.793
I'm holding up the bank,
and now's not the right time
to be ignoring my calls, okay?

32:42.828 --> 32:46.038
<i>I've got hostages.</i>
<i>I'm holding up the bank.</i>
You're not--

32:46.073 --> 32:50.240
<i>So, could you put my daughter</i>
<i>on the phone, please?</i>

32:50.275 --> 32:51.340
Thank you.

33:13.100 --> 33:14.099
<i> Daddy?</i>

33:14.860 --> 33:17.300
Hey, hey,
hey, baby girl.

33:17.335 --> 33:19.566
Don't hang up.
Don't hang up.

33:19.601 --> 33:20.633
Hey.

33:23.176 --> 33:26.474
I just wanted to let you know
that I love you, okay.

33:26.509 --> 33:29.378
Are you apologizing
and picking me up?

33:29.413 --> 33:33.217
<i>You gonna be mean to Daddy?</i>
<i>You ain't gonna give Daddy</i>
<i>a break?</i>

33:33.252 --> 33:35.417
<i>Baby, you know</i>
<i>I'll always tell you the truth.</i>

33:35.452 --> 33:38.123
And, uh, I hurt you.
I did.

33:38.158 --> 33:40.125
<i>Well, you shouldn't have</i>
<i>given me your word.</i>

33:40.160 --> 33:42.688
I apologize, baby.
<i>That's not telling the truth.</i>

33:42.723 --> 33:46.263
You hate when people
don't tell you the truth.
<i>I know. I know.</i>

33:46.298 --> 33:51.235
Baby, you know, sometimes
when people steal from you,
you've got no choice.

33:51.270 --> 33:52.731
You gotta get it back.

33:53.734 --> 33:56.669
And when I do,
I'm gonna get you a puppy.

33:58.805 --> 34:00.673
Are you for real?
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

34:00.708 --> 34:03.742
<i>Yes. That's the first thing</i>
<i>on my list.</i>

34:03.777 --> 34:07.482
Okay, call me when you're ready.
Love you. Bye.

34:07.517 --> 34:09.649
-Don't hang up. Hey.

34:10.882 --> 34:12.520
What did your father say?

34:12.554 --> 34:15.721
He got money,
so he's gonna get me
my puppy.

34:24.567 --> 34:26.303
Just like your damn mama.

34:42.453 --> 34:43.815
You look scared.

34:45.753 --> 34:47.126
You scared?

34:48.327 --> 34:49.425
I am.

34:54.201 --> 34:55.563
I told you...

34:58.403 --> 34:59.897
if I die today...

35:02.407 --> 35:03.571
I die alone.

35:19.457 --> 35:20.654
Come on, Easley.

35:46.319 --> 35:47.351
Hello?

35:47.386 --> 35:49.617
<i>Hi, is Bridget back yet?</i>

35:49.652 --> 35:52.620
Ma'am, the bank is being robbed.
I'm the one robbing it.
Do not call again!

35:56.021 --> 35:57.592
Come on, man.

35:58.529 --> 35:59.594
Come on.

36:20.518 --> 36:23.684
Kiah. Baby,
go back to your room.

36:23.719 --> 36:26.324
Why I gotta be
in my room, Mama?
Listen.

36:26.359 --> 36:29.426
When I know
what I need to know,
I'll let you know, okay?

36:29.461 --> 36:31.593
Please, baby.
Just go back
to your room.

36:34.499 --> 36:35.531
Thank you.

36:42.771 --> 36:45.541
Brian? Brian?

36:51.516 --> 36:55.617
My ex-husband-- same thing
happened to him almost.

36:57.852 --> 36:59.016
I, um--

37:00.085 --> 37:01.557
I'm scared.

37:03.990 --> 37:05.957
But I feel compassion
for you.

37:08.500 --> 37:11.402
You know,
my son and, uh, I...

37:13.373 --> 37:15.538
...we go to downtown Atlanta
on the weekends,

37:15.573 --> 37:17.408
pass out to the homeless.

37:20.908 --> 37:22.677
And they have stories.

37:25.517 --> 37:31.356
People judge.
They underestimate how folks
get in their position.

37:32.359 --> 37:33.820
I know stories like yours.

37:33.855 --> 37:35.888
They fought for the country,

37:35.923 --> 37:38.561
and they come here
and they don't get approved,
and I'm like...

37:39.729 --> 37:41.894
"I'm sorry."

37:41.929 --> 37:43.368
I'm sorry.

37:46.604 --> 37:47.669
Who's that?

37:50.377 --> 37:51.640
An old friend.

37:53.941 --> 37:56.007
It's your ex-husband.

37:57.846 --> 38:03.388
I mean, if-- if it is,
you probably should
hit him back.

38:03.423 --> 38:06.721
Ain't nothing
harder on the heart
than reaching out to an ex

38:07.526 --> 38:08.921
and not hearing
from them.

38:10.023 --> 38:11.726
I see you love your family.

38:11.761 --> 38:14.498
My close family.

38:14.533 --> 38:15.829
My daughter,

38:17.162 --> 38:18.469
Kiah.

38:21.870 --> 38:23.969
Maybe if you let us out,

38:24.004 --> 38:26.675
-we'll tell them
how good you been to us.
-They're not gonna kill me?

38:31.616 --> 38:33.044
They're not gonna kill me?

38:43.925 --> 38:46.090
Did you tell me
about your family
and your husband

38:46.125 --> 38:47.696
and your good times

38:47.731 --> 38:49.126
'cause you think
I'm a fool?

38:49.161 --> 38:52.536
-No.
-Try to soften me up?
Is that what it is?

38:52.571 --> 38:56.507
You think I'm dumb or slow?
Is that what it is?
No. Not at all.

38:56.542 --> 39:00.170
'Cause people be doing that
a lot. Thinking I'm a fool,
thinking I'm slow.

39:00.205 --> 39:02.579
I-- I don't know
if that's what
you was doing, ma'am.

39:02.614 --> 39:03.943
Brother, you're not a fool.

39:03.978 --> 39:07.914
I'm not a fool?
Okay. I'm not a fool.

39:09.214 --> 39:12.424
I'm just scared.

39:12.459 --> 39:14.690
That's all. Scared.

39:14.725 --> 39:15.889
Okay.

39:18.597 --> 39:19.926
I understand.

39:23.228 --> 39:26.471
You gonna turn the TV off.
This is not working.

39:39.244 --> 39:43.048
Did y'all just turn off the TV
in the bus-- in the business?

39:43.083 --> 39:45.985
You've got to let me know
what he's doing inside the bank.

39:46.020 --> 39:50.990
Excuse me if I'm not doing
exactly what you need of me.

39:51.025 --> 39:55.599
I don't know what
y'all are doing. We need someone
to negotiate with him now.

40:08.944 --> 40:11.241
Bernard!
Hey, how you doing?

40:11.276 --> 40:13.144
Riddick
is setting the perimeter.

40:13.179 --> 40:15.850
Wants the area clear
of any potential bombs
or co-conspirators.

40:15.885 --> 40:18.050
Okay.
We got four
SWAT units here.

40:18.085 --> 40:21.856
Cobb County PD, plus Marietta.

40:21.891 --> 40:23.957
Cobb sheriff's team is out.

40:23.992 --> 40:25.057
Got the dogs.

40:25.092 --> 40:27.224
Smyrna PD.

40:27.259 --> 40:29.501
We got the FBI, the GBI.

40:29.536 --> 40:31.635
Everybody here.
Got yourself a party.

40:34.266 --> 40:36.266
So how many snipers
we got?

40:36.301 --> 40:40.039
Uh, three units,
as I understand.

40:40.074 --> 40:42.943
But like I said,
there's a lot going on.

40:45.145 --> 40:48.916
-That's the new chief?
-Yeah. That's him.

41:07.640 --> 41:10.674
WSB-TV tip-line.
This is Lisa Larson.
What's your tip?

41:10.709 --> 41:12.643
<i>Hello, this is, uh,</i>
<i>Brian Brown-Easley.</i>

41:12.678 --> 41:15.877
<i>I'm heisting a Wells Fargo</i>
<i>on Windy Hills Road,</i>

41:15.912 --> 41:18.946
<i>and I have a bomb and hostages.</i>

41:18.981 --> 41:20.783
You're what?

41:20.818 --> 41:22.884
<i>Just calling</i>
<i>to let y'all know.</i>
Uh...

41:24.118 --> 41:26.052
You're at the Wells Fargo--

41:26.087 --> 41:27.757
You're at the Wells Fargo now,

41:27.792 --> 41:30.320
at the bank--
holding up the bank

41:30.355 --> 41:32.729
and you're calling us at WSB?

41:33.864 --> 41:35.996
<i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

41:36.031 --> 41:38.295
Uh, what was your name again,
sir, please?

41:38.330 --> 41:39.967
<i>My name is Brian Brown-Easley.</i>

41:40.002 --> 41:43.707
Brian Brown-Easley.

41:45.172 --> 41:48.074
Okay, you hold one sec.
<i>Okay.</i>

41:49.143 --> 41:52.210
I want you to sit here,
close to the camera.

41:54.346 --> 41:57.655
Lisa's got
the Windy Hill robber
on the line.

41:57.690 --> 41:59.118
All right, I'm hot.

42:01.056 --> 42:02.088
You got sound?

42:03.322 --> 42:04.794
Yeah, we're good.

42:05.830 --> 42:07.093
We're recording.

42:07.128 --> 42:09.865
Okay, thank you. Um--

42:09.900 --> 42:12.967
And how would you
like to be addressed?
Is it Brian?

42:13.002 --> 42:14.903
<i>Or-- Or Mr. Easley?</i>

42:14.938 --> 42:16.707
Brian's good.
<i>Okay, Brian.</i>

42:16.742 --> 42:19.303
Why are you holding up
a bank today, sir?

42:20.174 --> 42:22.779
<i>Because I'm a nobody to the VA.</i>

42:22.814 --> 42:25.012
You know,
just so we can verify
who you are,

42:25.047 --> 42:27.080
do you have
a social security number
or something?

42:27.115 --> 42:29.918
You trying to
steal my money too,
like the VA?

42:29.953 --> 42:32.217
<i>No, no, no.</i>
Trying to take my cash?

42:32.252 --> 42:35.055
No, I'm good.
I'm not trying
to steal your money.

42:35.090 --> 42:36.958
This is--
This is just so we can help.

42:36.993 --> 42:40.027
<i>Ma'am, just so you know,</i>
<i>I don't have a criminal record.</i>

42:40.062 --> 42:41.996
<i>I mean this is not</i>
<i>my day-to-day.</i>

42:42.031 --> 42:46.737
Well, but you say
you have bombs, right?
Where'd you get that?

42:46.772 --> 42:49.839
Oh, I can't give you
that information, ma'am.

42:49.874 --> 42:53.942
<i>Well, is it something</i>
<i>that could, you know,</i>
<i>level the bank?</i>

42:57.211 --> 42:59.211
Probably gonna
take out the whole room.

42:59.246 --> 43:00.751
<i>What kind of bomb?</i>

43:00.786 --> 43:03.347
Semtex.
<i>Semtex?</i>

43:04.724 --> 43:05.657
Take care now.

43:06.253 --> 43:07.989
You too.

43:16.967 --> 43:19.033
<i>Can we contact Wells Fargo</i>
<i>security</i>

43:19.068 --> 43:23.004
<i>and see if they have</i>
<i>the cameras inside</i>
<i>that we might be able to access?</i>

43:29.210 --> 43:30.341
Major Riddick.

43:32.048 --> 43:33.982
Sergeant,
you up to speed?
Indeed.

43:34.919 --> 43:36.413
Okay, we're ready
to conference in.

43:36.448 --> 43:39.383
We're conferencing in.

43:40.485 --> 43:42.155
Ma'am, I'm--
I'm not a thief.

43:42.190 --> 43:44.355
<i>Okay, I haven't taken anything</i>
<i>from the bank.</i>

43:44.390 --> 43:46.258
<i>I'm a decorated marine.</i>
<i>I'm a lance corporal.</i>

43:46.293 --> 43:48.161
Who's this on the phone?

43:48.196 --> 43:49.426
WSB-TV.

43:52.134 --> 43:54.805
So why is the suspect
talking to a reporter
and not us?

43:54.840 --> 43:57.434
We were just buying time
until you decided
to show up.

43:58.272 --> 43:59.711
<i>Two tours Iraq.</i>

43:59.746 --> 44:01.372
Camp Fox and Taqaddum.

44:02.947 --> 44:04.111
Honorable discharge.

44:04.146 --> 44:06.718
<i> Good for you, sir.</i>

44:06.753 --> 44:10.084
<i>And did you make friends?</i>
<i>You know, along the way</i>
<i>that you've kept up with?</i>

44:10.119 --> 44:11.723
<i> Yeah, I did,</i>

44:11.758 --> 44:14.286
but we lost contact,
you know.

44:14.321 --> 44:16.728
I don't really check in
with nobody or everybody
these days.

44:16.763 --> 44:18.125
I kinda stay to myself.

44:18.160 --> 44:20.864
<i>So the VA...</i>
<i>What's going on there?</i>

44:38.147 --> 44:40.213
Okay. Okay. Thanks.

44:40.248 --> 44:42.853
So it looks like this payment
was redirected

44:42.888 --> 44:46.318
to a college you're using
your GI Bill at,
to cure a deficit.

44:46.353 --> 44:48.518
Good news is,
you're all caught up
on payments.

44:48.553 --> 44:51.829
I was not behind on anything.
